  "why": "The paper describes mutations as in-memory floating-point perturbations (random noise, L∞-bounded changes, pixel-wise crossover/mutation) and reports implementation in Keras/TensorFlow, but it does not describe enforcing serialization-format constraints (e.g., clipping to [0,255], rounding to integer pixel precision, or otherwise generating inputs directly in a serialized image format). The mutation design focuses on keeping mutations small and on avoiding certain transformations that would produce 'invalid images', but there is no explicit statement that mutated inputs are clipped/rounded before storage or that tests are generated as serialized files. Therefore fault-inducing perturbations introduced in normalized/in-memory representations could be altered or lost when serialized, and the paper does not document measures to prevent that.",
